<subSubSection id="87C1B0F70045FFDFFF482A77116A30E5" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="475" pageId="15" pageNumber="474" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="CF64E37C0045FFDFFF482A77116A30E5" blockId="15.[151,1437,1723,2038]" lastBlockId="16.[151,1436,151,213]" lastPageId="16" lastPageNumber="475" pageId="15" pageNumber="474">
<emphasis id="FDAF3F6E0045FFC0FF482A7714D037B9" bold="true" box="[199,461,1903,1929]" pageId="15" pageNumber="474">Differential diagnosis.</emphasis>
Among Central American species, recognized by the combination of moderate size (ca. 3.00 mm), the densely punctate pronotum with the reliefs slightly less punctate than the depressions, and the male genitalia. This species has a generalized 
<taxonomicName id="08DB98FF0045FFC0FDD92AAF17CD37E1" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[598,720,1975,2001]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="474" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FDAF3F6E0045FFC0FDD92AAF17CD37E1" box="[598,720,1975,2001]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="474">Hydrochus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
habitus; reliable determinations will require dissection of males. The male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName id="08DB98FF0045FFC0FE042AC4171B37C5" box="[395,518,2011,2037]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="474" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="directus">
<emphasis id="FDAF3F6E0045FFC0FE042AC4171B37C5" box="[395,518,2011,2037]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="474">H. directus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is very slender, therefore superficially somewhat similar to that of 
<taxonomicName id="08DB98FF0045FFC0FB7E2AC4108137C5" authority="Perkins, 2021" authorityName="Perkins" authorityYear="2021" box="[1265,1436,2012,2037]" class="Insecta" family="Hydrochidae" genus="Hydrochus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="15" pageNumber="474" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aeruginosus" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis id="FDAF3F6E0045FFC0FB7E2AC4108137C5" box="[1265,1436,2012,2037]" italics="true" pageId="15" pageNumber="474">H. aeruginosus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="FDAF3F6E005AFFDFFF182D8F15CB3081" bold="true" box="[151,214,151,177]" pageId="16" pageNumber="475">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="E69C8215005AFFDFFF182D8F15CB3081" box="[151,214,151,177]" pageId="16" pageNumber="475" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
; however, details of the two distinctly differ, including shape and size of the parameres, size and shape of the basal piece, and form of the adbl. The habitus of the two species also distinctively differ.
</paragraph>
